Print:
    - make `from __future__ import print_function` valid rpython
    - make all the things use `print(x, y)`

Tuple arguments
    - remove use of `def foo((x, y), z)` - using decorator magic if needed

Exceptions:
    - remove references / use of multi-arg exceptions (raise Exc, Exc())

Leading zeros:
   - remove these, use octal literals if needed

Long integers:
   - use bit_length instead of long/int types
   - use six-style integer_types

Tuple args:
   - use decorator

Division
   - basic idea is to `from __future__ import division` / see what breaks

String / unicode
   - this will be a mess, no idea yet

Bytecode differences
